post_text:
Dear students in grades 8-12,
Jr/Sr High student schedules are now LIVE in SchoolTool. Grades 7/8 will be attending daily. However, students in grades 9-12 should pay particular attention to which cycle days they are scheduled to attend. The days are noted in the "Team" section as AC Silver Days or BD Black Days. More general details about Jr/Sr HS scheduling will be addressed at Thursday's virtual meeting. Links will be posted in the coming days on the district website.

Students in grades 8-12 may email Mr. Busch with any add/drop requests with the subject heading "Student Schedule". All concerns will be dealt with in the order they are received and may take until the first day of school for resolution. Add/Drop will as always be open thru the second Friday of the school year.

This is Lee Supensky, Interim Secondary Principal at Richfield Springs Central School

I‚Äôm calling to invite parents/guardians/caregivers of secondary students to a virtual question and answer session on Thursday, August 27th. This session will address student scheduling for the 2020-21 school year and will include Mr. Busch from the counseling department. Student schedules will be available on SchoolTool as early as this evening. Paper copies will be mailed Tuesday, Aug 25th.

The meetings will be offered through the google Meet link on the school's webpage as follows:
8th grade from 5:00-5:45
9th through 12th grade from 6:00- 6:45

As a reminder, 7th grade will hold its virtual transition meeting separately tomorrow night at 5pm.

Thank you

June 10 at 5:42 PM ¬∑

Thank you to the Senior Class, Administration, and Advisors for your collaboration in making the decisions needed regarding your graduation ceremony. Your thoughts, along with the Governor's guidelines, have allowed us to put together...

The Richfield Springs Central School's 131'st Commencement Ceremony!

*Graduation will be on Saturday June 27th and 10 a.m. outside of the school on our front lawn. Graduation rehearsal will be on Friday June 26th, beginning at 9 a.m.

*Each Senior will be allowed 5 guests to accompany them onto school grounds. Tickets will be given out, and ONLY THOSE WITH A TICKET will be allowed on school grounds.

*We are in the full blown planning process as we speak - more details will be released soon.

post_text: Congratulations to RSCS senior, Victor Gelfuso! Victor WON the State Level of the Oratorical Competition, winning a $6,000 scholarship! In the 83 year history of this competition, Victor is the FIRST Richfield Springs student to make it to Nationals! Unfortunately, due to the pandemic, the National Competition is cancelled for the year, so Victor will not be able to compete at that level. What a huge accomplishment for Victor! A special thank you to Leo Mackin and the Richfield Springs American Legion for their unrelenting support of RSCS.

post_text: We will continue to feed our students for free this summer. All students are eligible. If you would like to be added to the list to pick up at the school, just give us a call. If you live outside the village and would like home delivery, please return a copy of the waiver that is being sent out through School Messenger email. The form will also be available on the school website and Facebook page. There will be no meals for the week of June 29th to July 3rd and the program will conclude on August 31st.

Seniors will be meeting at the firehouse and will be following the fire truck(s) on a short route through the village and ending at the school.

We hope to fill the parking lot with parents and staff members, and the streets with our supportive community members- appropriately socially distancing from inside our cars.

As students progress through the bus loop in their cars, we have a little special something planned.

Seniors, staff and community members are encouraged to decorate their cars, make signs, etc.

Mrs. Simpson loves everything about Mexico. Its my absolute favorite place to vacation. Mr. & Mrs. Simpson have vacation club in Cancun, Mexico. We try to visit every year. Every year i share my love of Mexico with my students. We read stories, watch videos, sing and make a project. This year we are unable to do this together. I'd like to wish you all HAPPY CINCO DE MAYO! I shared my love of Mexico through our daily message in google classroom. Some students enjoyed the links to learn about Cinco de Mayo! I hope everyone enjoyed this fun day, as much as I do!

shared_text:
High School Happenings at RSCS
April 29 at 11:57 AM ¬∑

Attention Senior Students, Parents, and Family Members...

We have received many questions regarding graduation.
While we have not made any "formal" plans for this, as we are waiting for a directive from the Governor, we HAVE been working on a few things to show you how much we care!

1. We have ordered 2x4 ft banners of each senior's senior photo for the lamp posts to line Main Street. These will likely be up by the end of May.

2. We have ordered lawn signs (one for each parent- max 2 per family) of each senior also. These will likely be available by the end of May also.

3. We have a preliminary, socially distant appropriate, graduation plan in the works. We will share more specifics about this as we are given more specifics from our Governor. Please be assured, YOU WILL BE RECOGNIZED!!

4. Last, please remember this... "The only way to make sense out of change is to plunge into it, move with it, and join the dance." ~Alan Watts

#weareRICHFIELD
#SENIORS2020
#STRONG

post_text:
Update: Wednesday, March 25

Meal pickup at the school is from 10-12 outside the cafeteria on Monday, Tuesday - 4 meals (2 breakfast, 2 lunch), Thursday, Friday, as well as by bus delivery. Meals have been placed in plastic bags to be delivered at the front door to avoid person to person contact. We will continue to provide meals over Spring Break. Please call the school, if you would like to be added for delivery.

The Backpack program will take place this Friday, pickup at the school and delivery with the meals.

We will resume school work delivery on Thursday, March 26th. All work will be delivered, even in the village. This delivery will be ongoing and may take several days.

Students, please check your school emails.

Some other information,
‚Ä¢ There is WIFI access in the bus loop, feel free to swing by and there is no need to leave the car.
‚Ä¢ CSE meetings are still taking place through teleconference and videoconference
‚Ä¢ 3-8 Assessments are cancelled for this school year

Start your day with Art
March 17 at 9:00 AM ¬∑

Good morning. My name is Heather McCutcheon and I teach at Herkimer CSD in Herkimer, NY. This Lesson: Creating a ME is simple yet fun for any age. You can create the ME to be you, a family member, a character in a book or make it up. See what you can create! Use the video to follow the steps, along with handouts in the comments section. We will also be making deliveries in the mornings by bus route at the normal AM bus run time. Families are asked to send someone to the bus for pickup. Phone calls will be going out this afternoon, asking if families would like the meals delivered.

post_text:
It is with great pleasure that we announce the Richfield Springs Central School‚Äôs Valedictorian, Isabella Hudziak and Salutatorian, Jayce Horender.

Isabella Hudziak exemplifies persistence, kindness, and creativity. Isabella has participated in numerous creative activities including the writing club, the school play, editing the school newspaper and baking club. Her intention is to pursue a degree in secondary English education at Utica College.

Jayce Horender is passionate about the pursuit of knowledge, especially in regards to foreign language. Jayce one day hopes to become a professor or translator. Currently, he plans to attend SUNY Oswego.

We congratulate both students on their outstanding accomplishments and look forward to seeing what the future holds for them.

Now who‚Äôs ready for some softball and baseball??

shared_text:
Madison-Oneida BOCES
February 20 at 3:14 PM ¬∑

Dozens of students from across the region attended Women in Tech camp at MOBOCES today. The MORIC Model Schools team puts this event on for area 4th-8th grade girls. Today's special guest was WKTV Newschannel 2 Meteorologist Jill Reale , who showed the girls how to develop a forecast and use a green screen! Jill is also a fitness instructor and led the girls in a couple of dance routines during the day! It is safe to say they had a great day. Thanks, Jill! #techcamp #steam
